            <p>
                Dear {$IF_SALUTATION} {$IF_LAST_NAME},
            </p>
            <p>
                We are writing with regards to an unauthorized use of our client’s work on your website.
            </p>
            <p>
                LAPIXA is a copyright compliance agent which represents visual artists globally in
                matters of copyright infringement. Our image scanning software detected
                that {$PHFIRST_NAME} {$PHLAST_NAME}’s work is being used on the {$InfringerCompany}’s
                website at the following URL/s:
            </p>
            <p>
                {Opportunity.INFRINGEMENT_URL}
            </p>
            <p>
                {$PH_MRMS} {$PHLAST_NAME} identified your use as an infringement of {$PH_HISHER}
                copyright and submitted this case to LAPIXA to contact you with regards
                to the unauthorized continued use of {$PH_HISHER} work.
            </p>
            <p>
                Under the U.S. Copyright Act, 17 U.S.C. §101, et al. copyright holders are entitled
                to recover actual damages and any profits attributable to infringements,
                and should they hold Copyright Registration, before final judgement is
                rendered, are entitled to elect to recover an award of statutory damages
                of up to $30,000 per infringement.
            </p>
            <p>
                Please see a copy of the original photo and a screenshot of use attached to this
                letter.
            </p>
            <p>
                If you hold a valid license to this image, please provide this as soon as possible
                so we can update our records accordingly and withdraw our complaint.
            </p>
            <p>
                In the interest of avoiding litigation, we would like to offer you a retroactive
                license to cover the use which has already occurred on your website,
                subject to compliance with the following conditions by
                <strong>{Opportunity.CLOSE_DATE}.
                </strong>
            </p>
            <p>
                1. Immediate and permanent removal of all unauthorized uses of our client’s work
                from your website/s, including any and all social media sites, accounts,
                products &amp; marketing materials.
            </p>
            <p>
                2. Payment in full for the retroactive license fee of
                <strong>{Opportunity.CLAIM_AMOUNT} 
                </strong>for the copyrighted works (Exhibit A) used without authorization
                as shown in the screenshot (Exhibit B).
            </p>
            <p>
                Please note that removal of the image alone does not rectify the matter. Our client
                deserves fair compensation at the very least, for the use which has already
                occurred.
            </p>
            <p>
                We have calculated the above retroactive license using FotoQuote: The industry standard
                photo pricing guide. This is determined by taking into account elements
                such as; image size, duration, market size and type of usage. The price
                also includes an $85 administration fee. Payment instructions are found
                on the invoice attached to this letter. If you would like to continue
                to use the photograph/s, we would be happy to recalculate a license fee
                accordingly.
            </p>
            <p>
                LAPIXA operates within 12 different countries around the world alongside our network
                of lawyers. Failure to comply with the above conditions will result in
                the matter being appointed to our US attorney at which point this offer
                will no longer stand.
            </p>
            <p>
                If you have any questions, please email
                <a href="mailto:copyrightprotection@lapixa.com">
                    copyrightprotection@lapixa.com
                </a> or call 617-858-8400.
            </p>
            <p>
                Kind Regards,
            </p>
            <p>
                LAPIXA US Copyright Compliance Officer.
